      "message": "So at that point we have a client which has a proxy which has a reference to a string (since `Preserved \u003d\u003d false` by default)\n\nSince the temporary object is alive until the end of the full expression, and\n`.properties()` already creates the D-Bus message with the path copied into it,\nwe should be safe to use a temporary object as you suggested!\n\nHowever the API does not support temporary objects\n```\n/* Convert a non-Path instance to a Path instance. */\nauto path(auto\u0026 p) const noexcept\n          requires(!P)\n{\n     return client\u003cS, true, Preserved, Types...\u003e(ctx, proxy.path(p)); \n}\n```\n\nsince temporary objects do not bind to non-const reference.\n\n\nLet me know if the explanation is lacking or i missed anything.\n\nLong term the client and proxy should probably get an overload that directly support object_path.",
